$ Azure Data Lake Storage


{ Data Lake Storage Gen1 and Gen2

 { Gen1 #az-data-lake-storage-gen1

   Data Lake Storage Gen1 is an → development/Apache/Hadoop file system which is compatibel with → development/Apache/Hadoop/HDFS.

   Data stored in Gen1 can easily be analyzed with Hadoop frameworks such as → development/Apache/Hadoop/MapReduce[MapReduce] or Hive.

 }
 { Gen2 #az-data-lake-storage-gen2

   Gen2 merges Gen1 with → Microsoft/Azure/products/Blob-Storage and extends Blob Storage with *hierarchical namespaces*.

   Gen2 is the fundament to create → development/Data/lake[data lakes] in → Microsoft/Azure.

   See also the → Windows/PowerShell cmdLet noun → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/az/DataLakeGen2Item[`azDataLakeGen2Item`] 

 }

}

sa:
  The Azure Service *Data Lake Analytics*

  → Microsoft/Office/Excel menu → Microsoft/Office/Excel/GUI/Ribbon/tabs/Data/Get-and-Transform-Data/Get-Data[Data -> Get & Transform Data -> Get Data] -> From → Microsoft/Azure -> From Azure Data Like Storage

  Data in *Data Lake Storage* might be queried with → Microsoft/Azure/products/Data-Lake-Analytics#az-u-sql[U-SQL], which is the
  → development/Big-Data query language for → Microsoft/Azure/products/Data-Lake-Analytics.

  → development/Data/lake
